      <section eId="sec_CCRP-332">
        <num>CCRP 332</num>
        <heading>332.  Court order for arrest of defendant</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-332__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>There has been a breach of the bail undertaking.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-332__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>It appears that a surety has become insufficient, is dead, cannot be found, or has
ceased to meet the qualifications of law or does not own adequate immovable property
within the state.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-332__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court is satisfied that the bail should be increased or new or additional
security required.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112455</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
